techmeme.title: OpenAI warns that its upcoming models could pose a higher risk of enabling the creation of biological weapons and says it is stepping up testing of such models (Ina Fried/Axios)
Multiplier, which acquires accounting services firms and scales them with AI, raised $27.5M across a seed and Series A, with the latter led by Lightspeed (Marina Temkin/TechCrunch)
Iran's largest crypto exchange Nobitex says it was hacked, and pro-Israel group Predatory Sparrow claims responsibility; Elliptic: $90M+ was stolen and "burned" (Zack Whittaker/TechCrunch)
Meta is adding support for passkeys on Facebook's iOS and Android apps "soon", and will begin rolling out passkeys to Messenger "in the coming months" (Emma Roth/The Verge)
Wix acquires Base44, which lets users build apps from text prompts, for $80M; Base44 was founded by a solo entrepreneur six months ago and employs six people (Sophie Shulman/CTech)
